INSERT INTO c_content_master VALUES("59","How to Report Crime","<p>Botswana Police Service is grateful  to the citizens, business community, tourists/visitors and government employees  for their continued support and would  encourage anyone with information they feel may be relevant to Police to come forward.</p>\n<p>If you have been the victim of  crime, have witnessed a crime or  would  simply like to tell Police that a crime has been committed  there are several ways to do it. You can:</p>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Contact the nearest police station  in person or police officer in patrol</li>\n  <li>Dial either 999 (emergency number)  or toll free number or  Landline for that  police station</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You will be asked the following questions:</p>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Nature of the offence</li>\n  <li>Time of offence</li>\n  <li>Locality eg plot No, street, H/No or  any nearest structure </li>\n  <li>Identity of the suspect or physical  description of the suspect </li>\n  <li>Method of operation if known eg  weapon used</li>\n  <li>Witnesses where possible</li>\n  <li>The reporter should also request the  name of the officer received the report</li>\n  <li>The reporter should not temper with  the scene</li>\n  <li>The reporter should take into  consideration his/her own personal security and safety</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When reporting a crime it is  important to put your safety and the safety of other people first. In case you are not satisfied with the service or response,  ask for any senior officer in charge.</p>\n<p>Where possible preserve the scene of  crime. Contamination of crime scene might lead to loss of valuable evidence or  you might implicate yourself by leaving your fingerprints/DNA at the scene.</p>\n<p>PLEASE NOTE THE FOLLOWING: </p>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>In case of fire, bomb blasting, road  traffic accident it is important that service providers Police, Ambulance, Fire  Brigade etc have full and unhindered access to the crime scene or injured.</li>\n  <li>When reporting remember to remain  calm and exercise patience as the leading questions that are being asked at  time of reporting are to establish what is expected at the scene of crime.</li>\n  <li>You can report a crime anonymously  through your telephone. Your privacy or identity will not be revealed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Service Branches:</h3>\n<p>You may locate the service branche  in charge in the &nbsp;<a href=\\\"http://www.gov.bw/en/Ministries--Authorities/Ministries/State-President/Botswana-Police-Service-/Tools-and-Services/Ministry-Directory/?FromPageID=1590&FromPageType=1&pid=1&ClearSearch=true&Branch=-1\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Useful Links</a></p>\n     ","How to Report Crime","mcms","29","2017-11-14","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=59","","","18:36:01","0","","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master VALUES("60","Sexual Offenses","<p>Sexual offences of concern are rape, defilement, indecent   assault and incest. These are usually committed by friends or close   relatives. There are few cases where these offences are committed by   unknown people. Of the above offences, rape is the most common.   Perpetrators sometimes date victims to entertainment places and later   rape them. Due to excessive alcohol consumption, some victims realize   they have been raped when they wake up the following day. As for   defilement, young girls are enticed with money or valuable items to   consent to sexual acts.</p>\n<h3>Reporting rape</h3>\n<p>The incident should be immediately reported to the police. The sooner   an incident is reported to the police the more forensic evidence can be   collected, and this may help secure a conviction.</p>\n<br>\n<h3>Advantages of reporting rape</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>An opportunity to present your side of the story.</li>\n  <li>The attacker may be prosecuted.</li>\n  <li>Reporting a frequent attacker may stop future attacks.</li>\n  <li>The victim may receive medical assistance in time.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>NB: Reporting an incident does not mean the attacker will be prosecuted.</h4>\n<h3>Police Procedures regarding rape</h3>\n<p>All police investigations start with the collection of forensic   evidence. These tests are done by taking swabs from any part of your   body that the assailant came in contact with. It is important that you   do not do any of the following before the swabs are taken:</p>\n<p>Do not wash<br>\nDo not change your clothes</p>\n            ","Sexual Offenses","mcms","29","2017-11-14","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=60","","","18:37:52","0","","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master VALUES("61","Stock Theft","<p>Stealing of stock usually is committed by herd boys or syndicates,   incidents of stock are more common in areas that are close to urban   centres where there are lucrative markets for beef. Criminals, who   operate in syndicates, re-brand stolen cattle to defraud original   owners.</p>\n<h3>A lot of livestock is stolen due to the following reasons:</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Livestock left astray.</li>\n  <li>Livestock left unbranded and not earmarked</li>\n  <li>The responsibility is left solely with herd boys</li>\n  <li>Late or failure to pay herd boys accordingly</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Farmers are encouraged to form up into clusters so as to intensify   the fight against stock theft. Moreover, they are encouraged to take a   leading role in security of their livestock.</p>\n<h4>NB: The public is urged to report to the police people they suspect   to be operating livestock criminal syndicates and ascertain the   authenticity of any livestock before purchasing them.</h4>      \n      ","Stock Theft","mcms","29","2017-11-14","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=61","","","18:38:56","0","","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master VALUES("62","Trade and Liquor","<p>According to the Statutory Instrument No. 23 of 2008 which commenced   on the 1st April 2008, provides for the establishment of liquor control   authorities to provide powers, duties and functions and provide   comprehensive regulations of trade and liquor in Botswana.</p>\n<h3>Operation times for Bar</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Monday to Thursday from 1400 hours to 2200 hours, </li>\n  <li>Friday to Saturday from 1200 hours to 2300 hours, and </li>\n  <li>Sunday and public Holidays from 1500 hours to 2200 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Operation times for Bottle Stores</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Monday to Saturday from 1000 hours to 1900 hours, </li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Operation times for Clubs</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Monday to Thursday from 1400 hours to 2200 hours, </li>\n  <li>Friday to Saturday from 1200 hours to 2300 hours, and </li>\n  <li>Sunday and public Holidays from 1500 hours to 2200 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Operation times discotheque/Night club</h3>\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Monday to Thursday from 1900 hours to 0000 hours, </li>\n  <li>Friday to Saturday from 1900 hours to 0200 hours, and </li>\n  <li>Sunday and public Holidays from 1500 hours to 2200 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>TEMPORARY LIQUOR LICENSE</h3>\n<p>It is an authorization permitting the holder to sell intoxicating   liquor at a public place for consumption at such place for a period not   exceeding 90 days.</p>\n<table width=\\\"100%\\\" class=\\\"table table-borderless\\\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Trade Fair</td>\n      <td>Monday to Saturday</td>\n      <td>1200 - 1800 hours</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr> </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Festivals</td>\n      <td>Monday to Saturday</td>\n      <td>1400 - 0000 hours</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr> </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Picnics</td>\n      <td>Monday to Saturday</td>\n      <td>1200 - 1900 hours</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr> </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Other public activities</td>\n      <td>Monday to Saturday</td>\n      <td>1400 - 0000 hours</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr> </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<p>For More Information click here <a href=\\\"http://www.laws.gov.bw\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><strong>(http://www.laws.gov.bw)</strong></a></p>\n  ","Trade and Liquor","mcms","29","2017-11-14","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=62","","","18:40:04","0","","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master VALUES("69","Neighbourhood Watch","<h3>BPS is committed to ensuring that the community remains safe and secure.\nTips for Neighbourhood watch</h3>\n\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\n  <li>Form or join a neighbourhood watch scheme in your area</li>\n  <li>Keep your surroundings clear of bushes</li>\n  <li>Report faulty street lights to relevant authorities</li>\n  <li>Mark your valuable property </li>\n  <li>Report suspicious characters to the police</li>\n  <li>Note the telephones or cellphones of your neighbours so that you may call them should the need arise</li>\n</ul>","Neighbourhood Watch","mcms","31","2017-11-14","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=69","","","18:48:08","0","","","");
