INSERT INTO c_content_master_old VALUES("225","Public Relations Unit ","<p>The Branch which implements public service reform programs such as Work Improvement Teams (WITS), Performance Based Rewards System (PBRS), Systems Thinking, and Balance Score Card (BSC). The Branch has three units of Research and Development, Reforms and Public Relations.</p>\n<h3>1 Research</h3>\n<p>The unit conducts research on various policing issues, and provides findings to inform strategic decision making on crime.</p>\n<h3>2 Reforms</h3>\n<p>The Unit manages the change and productivity agenda of the organization through continuous improvement of process (PMS, WITS, Balance Score Card) and training police personnel in all strategic management processes.</p>\n<h3>3 Public Relations</h3>\n<p>As the organization&rsquo;s mouth piece, the Unit keeps the public informed about the BPS activities and services. It maintains beneficial relationships between the organization and its various publics with its publicity, promotions, advertising, research and media relations. Its major sections include Radio and Television, Publications as well as Research and Information.</p>\n<h3><em>3.1 Radio and Television</em></h3>\n<p>Radio and Television produces television programs (Itshireletse) and radio programs (Crime File) for broadcasting on Botswana Television and Radio Botswana.</p>\n<h3><em>3.2 Publications</em></h3>\n<p>The section produces publications such as the Police Magazine, billboards, posters, print adverts, brochures and banners that carry publicity materials.</p>\n<h3><em>3.3 Information and Research </em></h3>\n<p>Information and Research compiles and present factual or statistical information as requested by customers to support their stories, reports and studies. It also conducts audience surveys on its publicity programs to formulate messages that appeal specifically to targeted audiences.</p>\n<p>For more information about the Public Relations Unit, contact the Public Relations Officer at 3605439, 73102686 or email to police@gov.bw.</p>","Public Relations Unit ","mcms","11","2011-02-10","","Active","","bps-content.php?cid=225","","","09:34:17","0","0","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master_old VALUES("155","Mediation Services","<p>The Police Service is not only interested in criminal related issues, but a wide range of issues that the members of the public would like to be assisted with.  The Police are involved in mediation of disputes emanating from misunderstanding. Members of the public are encouraged to always come forth to the Police whenever they have disputes of any kind so as to seek mediation from the Police.  There are Social Welfare Officers based in at all the Police Stations who can help them solve their problems amicably.</p>","Mediation Services","mcms","4","2011-02-04","","Active","","","","","","0","0","","");
INSERT INTO c_content_master_old VALUES("156","Reporting a Missing Person","<p>A person is reported missing after 48 hours, and when making a report the following information should be given to the Police.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Names and age of the missing person </li>\n<li>Description of the missing person and mental status (sex, colour, height, body marks like tattoos, scars or any outstanding feature and what they were last seen wearing). </li>\n<li>Date and time he/she left home </li>\n<li>Photos can also be brought along. If a person is reported missing and at a later stage found, the police should be notified of such recovery.</li> </ul>","Report a Missing Person","mcms","4","2011-03-16","","Active","","","","","","0","0","","");
